#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: actors-cluster-self-health
description: Actor v1.23 — selfNode() + clusterHealth() single-node snapshot
---

# selfNode + clusterHealth — single-node

In a single-node process `selfNode()` returns the empty string (no
`startNode` was called) and `clusterHealth()` returns an empty map
(no connected peers).  Multi-node behaviour is exercised by the
integration suite; this conformance test pins the no-cluster branch
across INT/JS/JVM.

```scalascript
runActors {
  println("self='" + selfNode() + "'")
  // Pattern-match yields a typed binding so `.size` resolves on JVM.
  clusterHealth() match
    case m: Map[String, Double] => println("healthSize=" + m.size)
  println("ok")
}
```
